<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>H38-T005 AI Workflow Snapshot</title><style>body{font-family:Arial,sans-serif;line-height:1.45;color:#111827}h1{color:#0f172a}h2{border-bottom:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding-bottom:4px}table{border-collapse:collapse;width:100%;margin:12px 0}td,th{border:1px solid #cbd5e1;padding:8px;vertical-align:top}th{background:#e2e8f0}.note{background:#f8fafc;border-left:5px solid #0ea5e9;padding:10px;margin:12px 0}.small{font-size:12px;color:#475569}</style></head><body><h1>Highway 38 Solutions - AI Workflow Snapshot</h1><p><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T005<br><b>Package:</b> AI Workflow Snapshot<br><b>Scenario:</b> Repeated admin work to owner dashboard lite</p><p><img src="../assets/sample-ai-proof.svg" alt="AI workflow visual" style="width:100%;max-width:760px"></p><h2>Customer input received</h2><ul><li>Repeated tasks: reply to leads, chase missing info, build quote drafts, follow up after delivery.</li><li>Tools used: Gmail, Google Drive, Google Forms, Google Sheets.</li><li>Pain point: every customer request starts from scratch.</li><li>Goal: create a simple AI-assisted workflow without building a full app.</li></ul><h2>Workflow map</h2><table><tr><th>Step</th><th>Current pain</th><th>Recommended setup</th></tr><tr><td>Intake</td><td>Details arrive through texts and email.</td><td>Use one request form and one lead tracker.</td></tr><tr><td>Sort</td><td>Owner has to remember package and next step.</td><td>Use package/status columns and missing-info prompts.</td></tr><tr><td>Draft</td><td>Replies and quotes are rewritten every time.</td><td>Use reusable templates and prompt pack.</td></tr><tr><td>Track</td><td>Follow-ups get missed.</td><td>Use next-action and due-date dashboard.</td></tr><tr><td>Handoff</td><td>Delivery wording changes every job.</td><td>Use delivery email template with first action and upgrade path.</td></tr></table><h2>Prompt pack starter</h2><div class="note"><b>Missing-info prompt:</b> Turn this customer request into a short missing-information checklist. Separate facts, assumptions, and questions. Keep it friendly and direct.</div><div class="note"><b>Quote draft prompt:</b> Draft a quote reply using the service, customer goal, included items, not-included items, price range, timing, and next step.</div><div class="note"><b>Delivery prompt:</b> Write a customer handoff email summarizing the deliverable, first action, missing information, and optional next package.</div><h2>Dashboard fields</h2><table><tr><th>Field</th><th>Purpose</th></tr><tr><td>Lead status</td><td>New, Need Info, Quoted, Approved, In Build, Delivered.</td></tr><tr><td>Package</td><td>Problem Snapshot, Project Packet, AI Workflow, etc.</td></tr><tr><td>Next action</td><td>Owner knows what to do next.</td></tr><tr><td>Due date</td><td>Prevents stuck work.</td></tr><tr><td>Follow-up date</td><td>Prevents dead leads.</td></tr></table><p class="small">Highway 38 Solutions - Big problems. Clear plans. Hypothetical sample deliverable.</p></body></html>